cs.NI, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on the design and implementation of a programmable architecture for stateful packet processing in network switches, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of eXtended Finite State Machines (XFSM) as a low-level programming abstraction, which is related to the field of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also addresses platform independence, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses limitations and extensions, which is related to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
